<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="136" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,950,2093]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">
Phylogenetic reconstructions indicate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. Micheli ex Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[570,663,951,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eugenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[570,663,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Eugenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a consistently monophyletic group including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mattos" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="O. Berg" box="[1257,1402,950,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Calycorectes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1257,1402,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Calycorectes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other traditionally related genera (
<bibRefCitation author="Mazine, F. F. &amp; Souza, V. C. &amp; Sobral, M. &amp; Forest, F. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[510,720,986,1012]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="9497" refId="ref29199" refString="Mazine, F. F., Souza, V. C., Sobral, M., Forest, F. &amp; Lucas, E. (2014) A preliminary phylogenetic analysis of Eugenia (Myrtaceae: Myrteae), with a focus on Neotropical species. Kew Bulletin 69: 9497. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 014 - 9497 - x" type="journal article" year="2014">
Mazine 
<emphasis box="[601,656,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 2018; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bunger, M. O. &amp; Mazine, F. F. &amp; Forest, F. &amp; Bueno, M. L. &amp; Stehmann, J. R. &amp; Lucas, E. J." box="[798,1017,986,1013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="1209 - 1223" refId="ref27643" refString="Bunger, M. O., Mazine, F. F., Forest, F., Bueno, M. L., Stehmann, J. R. &amp; Lucas, E. J. (2016 a) The evolutionary history of Eugenia sect. Phyllocalyx (Myrtaceae) corroborates historically stable areas in the southern Atlantic forests. Annals of Botany 118: 1209 - 1223. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aob / mcw 209" type="journal article" year="2016">
Bünger 
<emphasis box="[886,941,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">et al.</emphasis>
2016a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Flickinger, J. A. &amp; Jestrow, B. &amp; Prieto, R. O. &amp; Santiago-Valentin, E. &amp; Sustache-Sustache, J. &amp; Campbell, K. C. S. E. &amp; Francisco-Ortega, J." box="[1027,1268,986,1012]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="448 - 480" refId="ref27901" refString="Flickinger, J. A., Jestrow, B., Prieto, R. O., Santiago-Valentin, E., Sustache-Sustache, J., Jimenez-Rodriguez, Campbell, K. C. S. E. &amp; Francisco-Ortega, J. (2020) A phylogenetic survey of Myrtaceae in the Greater Antilles with nomenclatural changes for some endemic species. Taxon 69: 448 - 480. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12263" type="journal article" year="2020">
Flickinger 
<emphasis box="[1148,1202,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). Nomenclatural adjustment has incorporated this phylogenetic framework into a new infrageneric arrangement of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mazine et al. 2016)" baseAuthorityName="Mazine" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eugenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1256,1349,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Eugenia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mazine, F. F. &amp; Bunger, M. O. &amp; Faria, J. E. Q. &amp; Lucas, E. &amp; Souza, V. C." pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="225 - 236" refId="ref29272" refString="Mazine, F. F., Bunger, M. O., Faria, J. E. Q., Lucas, E. &amp; Souza, V. C. (2016) Sections in Eugenia (Myrteae, Myrtaceae): nomenclatural notes and a key. Phytotaxa 289: 225 - 236. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 289.3.2" type="journal article" year="2016">
Mazine 
<emphasis box="[136,193,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This framework splits 
<taxonomicName box="[536,629,1059,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eugenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[536,629,1059,1084]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Eugenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into manageable groups, facilitating further taxonomic and conservation studies. Two species corresponding to 
<taxonomicName authority="(O. Berg) Mattos (2005: 3)" authorityName="Mattos" authorityPageNumber="3" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="O. Berg" box="[582,1205,1094,1121]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eugenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Calycorectes">
<emphasis box="[582,675,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Eugenia</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[746,891,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Calycorectes</emphasis>
(O.Berg) 
<bibRefCitation author="Mattos, J. R." box="[1011,1205,1094,1121]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref29146" refString="Mattos, J. R. (2005) Consideracoes sobre Calycorectes O. Berg. Loefgrenia 120: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2005">Mattos (2005: 3)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
were included in the phylogenetic study of 
<bibRefCitation author="Mazine, F. F. &amp; Souza, V. C. &amp; Sobral, M. &amp; Forest, F. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[390,625,1130,1156]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="9497" refId="ref29199" refString="Mazine, F. F., Souza, V. C., Sobral, M., Forest, F. &amp; Lucas, E. (2014) A preliminary phylogenetic analysis of Eugenia (Myrtaceae: Myrteae), with a focus on Neotropical species. Kew Bulletin 69: 9497. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 014 - 9497 - x" type="journal article" year="2014">
Mazine 
<emphasis box="[482,539,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
. That study suggests calyx fusion occurred only once in 
<emphasis box="[1271,1371,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">
<taxonomicName box="[1271,1367,1131,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eugenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Eugenia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
within the well-supported ‘clade 7’ sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Mazine, F. F. &amp; Souza, V. C. &amp; Sobral, M. &amp; Forest, F. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[545,789,1166,1192]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="9497" refId="ref29199" refString="Mazine, F. F., Souza, V. C., Sobral, M., Forest, F. &amp; Lucas, E. (2014) A preliminary phylogenetic analysis of Eugenia (Myrtaceae: Myrteae), with a focus on Neotropical species. Kew Bulletin 69: 9497. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 014 - 9497 - x" type="journal article" year="2014">
Mazine 
<emphasis box="[640,701,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Giaretta, A. &amp; Amorim, B. S. &amp; Sano, P. T. &amp; Souza, G. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[804,1064,1166,1192]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="66 - 73" refId="ref28086" refString="Giaretta, A., Amorim, B. S., Sano, P. T., Souza, G. &amp; Lucas, E. (2019 a) Phylogenetic placement of new species with fused calyx reveals homoplastic character in Eugenia (Myrtaceae). Systematic Botany 44: 66 - 73. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364419 X 697903" type="journal article" year="2019">
Giaretta 
<emphasis box="[905,966,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">et al.</emphasis>
(2019a)
</bibRefCitation>
explored the phylogenetic signal of calyx fusion within 
<taxonomicName box="[406,499,1203,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eugenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[406,499,1203,1228]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Eugenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using phylogenetic reconstruction based on five DNA regions (one nuclear; four plastid). 
<bibRefCitation author="Giaretta, A. &amp; Amorim, B. S. &amp; Sano, P. T. &amp; Souza, G. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[234,482,1238,1264]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="66 - 73" refId="ref28086" refString="Giaretta, A., Amorim, B. S., Sano, P. T., Souza, G. &amp; Lucas, E. (2019 a) Phylogenetic placement of new species with fused calyx reveals homoplastic character in Eugenia (Myrtaceae). Systematic Botany 44: 66 - 73. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364419 X 697903" type="journal article" year="2019">
Giaretta 
<emphasis box="[331,388,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">et al.</emphasis>
(2019a)
</bibRefCitation>
demonstrate that calyx fusion in 
<taxonomicName box="[855,948,1239,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eugenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[855,948,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Eugenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is homoplastic and recover a well-supported 
<taxonomicName authority="O. Berg (1856 a: 204)" authorityName="O. Berg" authorityPageNumber="204" authorityYear="1856" box="[136,696,1274,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eugenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Umbellatae">
<emphasis box="[136,229,1275,1300]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Eugenia</emphasis>
section 
<emphasis box="[324,455,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Umbellatae</emphasis>
O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Berg, O. C." box="[486,696,1274,1301]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="129 - 384" refId="ref27469" refString="Berg, O. C. (1856 a) Revisio Myrtacearum huc usque cognitarum s. Klotzschii &quot; Flora Americae aequinoctialis &quot; exhibens Myrtaceas. Linnaea 27: 129 - 384." type="journal article" year="1856">Berg (1856a: 204)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
including 
<taxonomicName authority="O. Berg (1856 a: 317)" authorityName="O. Berg" authorityPageNumber="317" authorityYear="1856" box="[816,1230,1274,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Calycorectes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandifolius">
<emphasis box="[816,987,1274,1301]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">C. grandifolius</emphasis>
O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Berg, O. C." box="[1018,1230,1274,1301]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="129 - 384" refId="ref27469" refString="Berg, O. C. (1856 a) Revisio Myrtacearum huc usque cognitarum s. Klotzschii &quot; Flora Americae aequinoctialis &quot; exhibens Myrtaceas. Linnaea 27: 129 - 384." type="journal article" year="1856">Berg (1856a: 317)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[1284,1332,1275,1301]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Giaretta et al. 2019 b)" baseAuthorityName="Giaretta" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[136,535,1310,1337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Calycorectes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,281,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Calycorectes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Giaretta, A. &amp; Vasconcelos, T. N. C. &amp; Mazine, F. F. &amp; Faria, J. E. Q. &amp; Flores, R. &amp; Holst, B. &amp; Sano, P. T. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[294,528,1310,1337]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="106553" refId="ref28155" refString="Giaretta, A., Vasconcelos, T. N. C., Mazine, F. F., Faria, J. E. Q., Flores, R., Holst, B., Sano, P. T. &amp; Lucas, E. (2019 b) Calyx (con) fusion in a hyper-diverse genus: Parallel evolution of unusual flower patterns in Eugenia (Myrtaceae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 139: 106553. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2019.106553" type="journal article" year="2019">
Giaretta 
<emphasis box="[392,447,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">et al.</emphasis>
2019b
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In light of those results, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mattos" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="Kausel" box="[810,1008,1310,1336]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Schizocalomyrtus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[810,1008,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Schizocalomyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was selected as an appropriate name for ‘clade 7’, i.e. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kausel) Mattos (2005: 3)" authorityName="Mattos" authorityPageNumber="3" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="Kausel" box="[290,944,1346,1373]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eugenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Schizocalomyrtus">
<emphasis box="[290,383,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Eugenia</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[448,646,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Schizocalomyrtus</emphasis>
(Kausel) 
<bibRefCitation author="Mattos, J. R." box="[756,944,1346,1373]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref29146" refString="Mattos, J. R. (2005) Consideracoes sobre Calycorectes O. Berg. Loefgrenia 120: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2005">Mattos (2005: 3)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Giaretta, A. &amp; Vasconcelos, T. N. C. &amp; Mazine, F. F. &amp; Faria, J. E. Q. &amp; Flores, R. &amp; Holst, B. &amp; Sano, P. T. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[958,1192,1346,1373]" pageId="1" pageNumber="136" pagination="106553" refId="ref28155" refString="Giaretta, A., Vasconcelos, T. N. C., Mazine, F. F., Faria, J. E. Q., Flores, R., Holst, B., Sano, P. T. &amp; Lucas, E. (2019 b) Calyx (con) fusion in a hyper-diverse genus: Parallel evolution of unusual flower patterns in Eugenia (Myrtaceae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 139: 106553. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2019.106553" type="journal article" year="2019">
Giaretta 
<emphasis box="[1057,1114,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">et al.</emphasis>
2019b
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1309,1346,1372]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1848,1870]" captionTargetBox="[244,1344,190,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[244,1344,190,1824]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Diversity of Eugenia sect. Schizocalomyrtus. A–B. Eugenia acutata. A. Auxotelic inflorescence undergoing a second phase of vegetative growth. B. Flowers at anthesis. C–D. Eugenia tenuipedunculata. C. Flowers. D. Immature fruits. E. Eugenia neoriedeliana. Flower opening via transversal tearing at the calyx base resulting in a calyptra-like structure. F. Eugenia guanabarina. Flowers opening via transversal tearing at the calyx base resulting in a calyptra-like structure (S) placed in opposition to a petal (P). G–H. Eugenia longohypanthiata. G. Flower bud tearing irregularly at anthesis. H. Immature fruits crowned by the remnant of the calyx lobes (S) and the hypanthium (H). (A–B: A. Giaretta 1460; C: J.E.Q. Faria 1000; D: A. Giaretta 1493; E: A. Giaretta 1489; F: A. Giaretta 1035; G: A. Giaretta 1500; H: A. Giaretta 1502). Photos by A. Giaretta, except C by J.E.Q. Faria." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649290/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="136">Figure 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
